While it is considered an unladylike, dirty, and mysterious pursuit Mary Anning a poor English young woman has the 'eye' for finding these collectables then selling them to help support her poor family. Three sisters move to Lyme Regis where Mary lives. The older Miss Philpot becomes fast friends with Mary as they begin to scan the beaches together in their pursuit of fossil hunting. The love life of sister Margaret, the sorrow of the poor family of Mary's, and the soothing behavior of sister Louise all add to an adventure of finding some of the earliest whole fossils specimens for England's museums.
